# Testing & CI

- Behavior changes → targeted tests first, then domain regression.
- Do not weaken assertions to green CI; explain environment-only failures (e.g. local Postgres).
- New backend tests: `*_new` suffix per project convention.

## Canonical checks

```bash
python3 -m compileall routers services schemas models tests -q
.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/test_alembic_single_head_new.py -q --no-cov
.venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/<domain> -q --no-cov
npm --prefix frontend test -- --run
npm --prefix frontend run build
git diff --check
```

## CI fixes

Root cause from `gh run view` logs; no skipping hooks/tests unless user asks.
